1.A : Mindful AI Company 

1.B.1  : Goals

At MindfulAI, we aim to deliver professional grade psychological support at affordability and scale. We are developing a global mental health companion powered by AI, delivered at scale to support people in managing mental wellness. This AI powered mental health companion will incorporate evidence-based techniques from CBT and support for crisis intervention. It will also enable users to monitor their mental wellness over time. Our main goals are to close the global treatment gap for mental health by providing access to mental health support for people with no current access, to support traditional therapists as a useful companion in between sessions, to act as a gateway for those afraid of traditional therapy, and to deliver AI powered mental health support that is built with strong ethical considerations, that is clinically validated, and that securely protects user privacy.

Meyer Mental Health plans to reach 10 million users within the next 5 years, using psychology-backed techniques to make a positive difference in users’ mental health. We are currently working with over 50 organizations such as mental health companies, clinicians, hospitals and healthcare providers around the world who use our technology and collaborate with us to achieve our mission. Long-term, we hope our technology and techniques will contribute to lowering the stigma associated with mental health and help more people receive early intervention for common issues such as stress, anxiety, and depression.

1.B.2 : Idea Origination

Our founding team has personal experiences with loved ones struggling to find access to affordable, stigma free mental health services. As we continued to study AI Ethics and Healthcare Applications in graduate school, we decided to take our experiences and research and create a platform to help address the mental health needs of individuals across the world. After thorough research into AI in mental health, we found that while there are numerous applications that utilize natural language processing, human emotion recognition, and other ML capabilities in mental health, most have significant room for improvement with regards to ethics. Thus, the seed was planted for what would eventually become MindfulAI.

MindfulAI is built on the basis of research carried out by the World Health Organisation (WHO) which found that 75% of people suffering from mental health in low and middle-income countries receive no treatment at all. But in high-income countries where therapy is available, long waiting times of months can mean that people are forced to wait for help. We knew that simply throwing more money at existing, flawed mental health AI solutions was not going to be enough, particularly if they continued to embed new biases, promote unhealthy dependency and offer poor quality advice.

1.B.3: Purpose/Values/Mission

Our mission: To provide greater access to evidence-based mental health support through the use of ethically-designed AI, while still emphasizing the importance of human connection and support.

Core Values:
- Human-Centered Design: All of our features are designed starting from real human needs and not from cool features that can be technically implemented. We work with mental health professionals, patients and the community from the very beginning of our design process.
- Radical Transparency: We want to be transparent about the capabilities and limitations of our AI, as well as the reasoning behind its decisions and when a human professional should be brought in. We will not abuse our potential for commercial gain to overhype our technology.
- Privacy as a Basic Right: Your mental health records are some of the most personal data possible, so we treat them with appropriate respect and rigour. We've designed Healthwatch from the ground up with privacy in mind, and include as many options as possible to allow you to share just as much or as little health information with your support team as you like.
- Clinical Validity: eLift uses a very strict and traditional approach to clinical validity of interventions by integrating with leading research centers to validate eLift Interventions through peer reviewed studies to assure the clinical validity of results.
- Inclusive Accessibility: We have attempted to include individuals of various cultures, language proficiency, physical and cognitive ability, and socioeconomic status in the design of our technology in order to avoid increasing healthcare disparities.

Our mission: To provide compassionate, accessible and evidence-based, AI-powered mental health solutions that support and augment traditional care to reduce barriers to care and give anyone, anywhere the power to manage the ups and downs of life and build mental strength.

1.B.4 Key Questions
Our ethical touchstone for product decisions: How do we use AI to build something good, not bad, and not addictive?At AI For Good, our guiding ethical principle is to design products that empower users with autonomy, and foster their well-being. Our goal is to ensure that using our products help users grow and thrive, as opposed to creating a new unhealthy addiction to technology. This means constantly challenging ourselves on the outcomes we are trying to achieve with our product features, and ensuring those outcomes matter. Unlike time spent using our product, these outcomes measure if users are actually getting better as a result of using it.

2. How do you make sure your AI-powered mental health product scales but also provides the human connection that matters most to users seeking mental health support? This is one of the questions that have guided our product and marketing efforts. We have consistently tried not to mistake AI for therapists and instead have explored how AI can be a useful complement to therapists to reach more people. We are actively experimenting with a hybrid model where AI processes messages, AI identifies situations where a therapist is needed and alerts both the user and the therapist, and human conversation can occur at anytime support is needed.

3. What safeguards and governance structures will ensure that as your startup grows, becomes more commercial and under pressure to scale, that you stay true to the values and mission that drove you to start the company in the first place? This question is designed to test your awareness of the pressure points that a startup will go through as it grows. My experience at Lending Club was that we designed many of these safeguards into the company structure before they became problems. For example, Lending Club has an independent ethics board, a user advocate, etc.


Objective: Development and evaluation of clinically effective AI powered therapy chatbot for treatment of mild to moderate levels of anxiety and/or depression.

Key Results:
1. By mid-2027 deliver a fully functioning platform using at least 20 different methods that have evidence-based support.
2. Achieve self-reported reduction in symptoms of mental health issues in 70% of users in our initial pilot study of 500 users by end of 2027.
